      "content": "I'd still caution against using the eye drops without knowing the underlying cause of your symptoms. Overuse can lead to further irritation or may mask underlying conditions, risking potential harm. It's crucial to seek a proper diagnosis and guidance from a healthcare professional, as self-diagnosing and treating eye conditions can be quite risky. Use the drops as directed for mild dryness, but don't ignore the symptoms or push for self-diagnosis. Your eye health is incredibly important.",
